WEBVTT

00:07.355 --> 00:09.531
<i>narrator: Previously on</i> <i>
"The Thing About Pam."</i>

00:09.574 --> 00:11.141
We're behind on the mortgage.

00:11.185 --> 00:13.491
That's all that's left.
Betsy's insurance.

00:13.535 --> 00:17.626
Court finds the defendant,
Russell Faria, not guilty.

00:17.669 --> 00:20.107
Seems I'm not the only one
with a bad reputation.

00:20.150 --> 00:21.804
<i>It's Cathy Singer</i> <i>
from "Dateline."</i>

00:21.847 --> 00:23.545
You stopped answering my texts.

00:23.588 --> 00:24.850
Say hi to Cathy.

00:24.894 --> 00:26.852
Everybody's treated me
like I killed Betsy

00:26.896 --> 00:27.897
'cause that's what the TV says.

00:27.940 --> 00:29.159
We all talk about it.

00:29.203 --> 00:30.856
No one could've done it
but you.

00:30.900 --> 00:34.425
<i>The whole town has turned</i> <i>
their backs on me.</i>

00:34.469 --> 00:36.514
When there's stuff in your way,

00:36.558 --> 00:40.214
<i>what you gotta do</i> <i>
is get rid of it.</i>

00:46.263 --> 00:53.531
<i>♪</i>

01:08.155 --> 01:10.374
Mrs. Hupp?

01:10.418 --> 01:12.724
Mrs. Hupp, you okay in there?

01:17.468 --> 01:19.166
Mrs. Hupp, if you
don't respond immediately,

01:19.209 --> 01:21.951
we're coming in.

01:21.994 --> 01:23.779
I'm good.

01:23.822 --> 01:25.737
<i>♪</i>

01:28.784 --> 01:33.702
<i>♪</i>

01:33.745 --> 01:37.358
Every single killer
in every single book

01:37.401 --> 01:40.926
gets caught for the same
stupid reason,

01:40.970 --> 01:43.581
keeping stuff, things.

01:43.625 --> 01:48.238
You know, little things
from the people they kill.

01:48.282 --> 01:51.807
Do you believe that?
It's like, "Hello, idiot."

01:51.850 --> 01:56.681
Just don't keep
their driver's license,

01:56.725 --> 01:59.423
or tufts of hair,

01:59.467 --> 02:02.818
and you get away with it.

02:03.688 --> 02:06.300
You and your murder books.

02:07.127 --> 02:08.432
Ugh.

02:08.476 --> 02:10.086
It's not wide enough.

02:10.130 --> 02:13.176
I told you to get the big roll

02:13.220 --> 02:16.005
to save money.

02:16.919 --> 02:19.748
Oh, you guys better
get going to St Louis.

02:19.791 --> 02:21.358
Big job today, right?

02:21.402 --> 02:23.447
Full renovation.

02:23.491 --> 02:26.798
Don't hurry back.
I got plenty to handle here.

02:26.842 --> 02:28.191
Yeah, what's that mean?

02:28.235 --> 02:29.453
I'm so tired
of people looking at me

02:29.497 --> 02:30.976
like I'm some monster.

02:31.020 --> 02:32.326
I mean, it's whatever,

02:32.369 --> 02:33.936
but it's screwing
with our business.

02:33.979 --> 02:35.155
What am I supposed to do

02:35.198 --> 02:38.027
if nobody wants
the Derby house?

02:38.070 --> 02:40.682
We're losing money.

02:40.725 --> 02:43.685
Somebody's gotta do something
about that.

02:44.512 --> 02:47.515
Well, maybe I should just
stick around here today.

02:50.387 --> 02:51.606
No, no, no, no, no, no.

02:51.649 --> 02:53.129
It's my problem.
I'll deal with it.

02:53.173 --> 02:54.435
Just bring me back
some of those--

02:54.478 --> 02:57.699
those chocolate things
I like, okay?

02:57.742 --> 02:59.179
What are you gonna
do with that anyway?

02:59.222 --> 03:00.267
- Hmm?
- That.

03:00.310 --> 03:01.746
What are you gonna do with it?

03:01.790 --> 03:04.923
It's like a rug now.
See?

03:04.967 --> 03:07.274
Little baby rug.

03:07.317 --> 03:09.841
Okay.
See you later.

03:09.885 --> 03:11.887
Drive safe.

03:13.932 --> 03:18.241
<i>narrator: What's the advantage</i> <i>
of camouflage in the wild?</i>

03:18.285 --> 03:20.852
<i>Can one creature pose</i> <i>
as another?</i>

03:20.896 --> 03:24.682
<i>Can a leopard</i> <i>
change its spots?</i>

03:24.726 --> 03:28.904
<i>Can Pam become someone else?</i>

03:31.950 --> 03:39.001
<i>♪</i>

04:41.324 --> 04:43.761
Hey.

04:43.805 --> 04:46.764
You wanna make some easy money?

04:47.896 --> 04:49.332
My name's Cathy.

04:49.376 --> 04:52.074
I'm a producer at that show,
"Dateline."

04:52.117 --> 04:54.424
- Okay?
- So we're looking for people

04:54.468 --> 04:57.601
to re-enact soundbites
and 911 calls.

04:57.645 --> 04:59.473
We'll give you $1,000

04:59.516 --> 05:01.779
just to come with us
and record it.

05:01.823 --> 05:02.867
Cash.

05:02.911 --> 05:05.827
No paper trail
back to Uncle Sam.

05:05.870 --> 05:08.830
That sound like something
you'd be interested in doing?

05:08.873 --> 05:10.962
So you're just driving around

05:11.006 --> 05:12.573
looking for people
to say some lines?

05:12.616 --> 05:14.618
Well, soundbites
are actually, uh,

05:14.662 --> 05:17.447
redoing, um, actual calls.

05:17.491 --> 05:19.580
Yeah, I know
what sound bites are.

05:19.623 --> 05:21.495
I'm just--don't understand

05:21.538 --> 05:24.498
why you're driving around
picking up random people.

05:24.541 --> 05:27.892
Real people sound more real.

05:28.850 --> 05:30.939
1,000 bucks.

05:32.027 --> 05:34.029
Cash, tax-free.

05:37.162 --> 05:38.381
Let me, uh--

05:38.425 --> 05:40.601
let me put up my dog.

05:42.385 --> 05:45.388
Come here.
Come here, Moose. Let's go.

05:46.868 --> 05:49.392
Oh, and you, uh,
you can't bring your, uh,

05:49.436 --> 05:52.003
your wallet or your phone.

05:52.047 --> 05:57.095
The big bosses, they don't like
clutter and stuff.

05:57.139 --> 06:00.534
Oh, no keys
or cigarettes, neither.

06:00.577 --> 06:02.318
Just bring you.

06:02.362 --> 06:04.364
<i>narrator:</i> <i>
"Dateline" does not pay people</i>

06:04.407 --> 06:06.670
<i>to record sound bites.</i>

06:06.714 --> 06:09.978
<i>So what was Pam up to?</i>

06:13.024 --> 06:17.681
<i>♪</i>

06:17.725 --> 06:19.509
Where'd you say
we were going again?

06:19.553 --> 06:22.251
Oh, they rented a trailer,
"Dateline."

06:22.294 --> 06:25.254
They talked to the manager.
Got one of those new ones.

06:25.297 --> 06:26.864
They talked to Kent?

06:26.908 --> 06:29.693
Uh, yep, Kent.

06:30.302 --> 06:32.914
Well, we passed his trailers.

06:32.957 --> 06:36.047
Ugh, brain's all twisted-up
pretzel or something.

06:36.091 --> 06:37.701
The trailer is tomorrow.

06:37.745 --> 06:39.224
Keep changing the place on me.

06:39.268 --> 06:42.140
Today, they rented a house
over by Lake St Louis.

06:42.184 --> 06:44.055
<i>Past all the shops and</i> <i>
all that. Doesn't matter.</i>

06:44.099 --> 06:46.623
<i>Anyway, we gotta get there</i> <i>
fast as we can</i>

06:46.667 --> 06:48.886
<i>so I can run</i> <i>
the first lady home.</i>

06:48.930 --> 06:50.671
She just finished her lines.

06:50.714 --> 06:53.500
Then I'll circle back
and--and take you home.

06:53.543 --> 06:57.547
So they just got producers
driving all around the country

06:57.591 --> 06:59.636
picking people up?
- Oh, yeah.

06:59.680 --> 07:03.248
Back and forth between
- St. Lou and Chi-
- Town.

07:03.292 --> 07:04.249
But I don't mind.

07:04.293 --> 07:06.295
I like driving.

07:06.338 --> 07:07.470
Good for the feet.

07:13.955 --> 07:16.914
<i>♪</i>

07:16.958 --> 07:19.003
You know, I didn't know
we was going so far.

07:19.047 --> 07:21.049
I gotta take my brother
to the doctor.

07:21.092 --> 07:22.703
Oh, this'll be quick.
Just say a couple things

07:22.746 --> 07:23.791
and then I'll run you home.

07:23.834 --> 07:25.619
Yeah, he don't have a car.

07:25.662 --> 07:27.664
He--he needs me to pick him up.
- Where's he live?

07:27.708 --> 07:29.318
We could grab him and--
and drop him off

07:29.361 --> 07:31.755
and then I could get you back
to--to make your money.

07:31.799 --> 07:32.930
I thought you had
to rush back

07:32.974 --> 07:34.192
to pick up that other person.

07:34.236 --> 07:37.413
Other guy can wait a bit.

07:37.457 --> 07:38.414
The lady.

07:38.458 --> 07:40.416
Yeah, the lady.

07:40.460 --> 07:47.641
<i>♪</i>

07:50.731 --> 07:53.385
Uh, I'm real sorry.

07:53.429 --> 07:55.475
- I--
- I left my door unlocked.

07:55.518 --> 07:58.086
I really gotta get back.

07:58.129 --> 08:01.916
Aw, and miss out
on 1,500 bucks?

08:01.959 --> 08:05.354
Well, you must be super rich
or something.

08:05.397 --> 08:06.964
You super rich?

08:07.008 --> 08:10.490
<i>♪</i>

08:10.533 --> 08:11.752
I'm sorry.

08:11.795 --> 08:13.580
Appreciate the offer.

08:13.623 --> 08:15.582
Take me back.

08:15.625 --> 08:18.715
<i>♪</i>

08:22.023 --> 08:29.073
<i>♪</i>

08:38.213 --> 08:40.650
911, what's your emergency?

08:40.694 --> 08:42.086
Uh, there's this woman.

08:42.130 --> 08:44.132
Says her name is Cathy
from the show "Dateline"

08:44.175 --> 08:45.829
and she's driving around
my neighborhood

08:45.873 --> 08:48.702
offering people money
to get in her car.

08:48.745 --> 08:50.878
- Yeah, and I just--
- I just--

08:50.921 --> 08:54.359
it's like really weird
and maybe dangerous.

08:54.403 --> 08:56.274
<i>narrator:</i> <i>
Some predators give up</i>

08:56.318 --> 08:59.582
<i>when their prey escapes.</i>

08:59.626 --> 09:03.151
<i>Others get hungrier.</i>

09:06.067 --> 09:13.074
<i>♪</i>

09:16.120 --> 09:20.342
<i>Nasty and brutish,</i> <i>
the laws of nature demand</i>

09:20.385 --> 09:23.824
<i>that desperate hunters</i> <i>
track down the one</i>

09:23.867 --> 09:27.044
<i>separated from its herd.</i>

09:27.088 --> 09:29.873
<i>♪</i>

09:29.917 --> 09:32.223
Hey!
Hey, guy.

09:32.267 --> 09:34.617
<i>♪</i>

09:34.661 --> 09:38.229
You want to make $1,000?

09:38.273 --> 09:39.666
Cash?

09:39.709 --> 09:46.673
<i>♪</i>

09:46.716 --> 09:49.240
Great.

09:56.160 --> 10:03.428
<i>♪</i>

10:13.743 --> 10:16.398
Okay. And, uh, here.

10:16.441 --> 10:19.009
<i>♪</i>

10:19.053 --> 10:21.664
You gotta put this
in your pocket for the--

10:21.708 --> 10:23.927
for the recording.

10:23.971 --> 10:26.887
Your pocket--this in your--

10:26.930 --> 10:28.584
can you give me your pocket?

10:28.628 --> 10:30.630
Here we go. Great.

10:30.673 --> 10:32.675
Okay.

10:32.719 --> 10:34.590
Let's go.

10:36.026 --> 10:37.637
<i>So it's just that one line,</i>

10:37.680 --> 10:40.422
but you gotta get it right
on the first try, okay?

10:40.465 --> 10:42.554
I mean, I'm gonna, you know,
say it with you

10:42.598 --> 10:44.556
a bunch of times
before we get there,

10:44.600 --> 10:46.602
make sure you can
keep all that cash.

10:46.646 --> 10:48.299
That's a lot of cash.

10:48.343 --> 10:50.911
So go ahead.
Say it back to me.

10:50.954 --> 10:52.608
It's just that one line.

10:52.652 --> 10:56.743
"Do you want me to do to you
what we did to Russ' wife?"

10:56.786 --> 10:57.744
Go ahead.

10:57.787 --> 10:59.833
<i>♪</i>

10:59.876 --> 11:02.139
Hey!

11:06.143 --> 11:08.276
If you wanna keep that money,

11:08.319 --> 11:10.060
you're gonna have to say it

11:10.104 --> 11:12.672
and you're gonna have
to say it perfect.

11:13.760 --> 11:17.677
And you're gonna hold this
when they record you, okay?

11:17.720 --> 11:20.375
Just like that.

11:20.418 --> 11:22.290
Well, maybe you practice
with it,

11:22.333 --> 11:24.292
but I gotta hear you
say the line

11:24.335 --> 11:25.554
before we get there

11:25.597 --> 11:27.948
or I can't give you
the money, okay?

11:27.991 --> 11:29.993
It's rules and stuff.

11:30.037 --> 11:32.082
S--sorry.

11:32.126 --> 11:34.041
Heck's wrong with you?

11:34.084 --> 11:36.739
Car accident.
Long time ago.

11:36.783 --> 11:39.002
B--bad.

11:41.222 --> 11:42.789
Fine. Fine.

11:42.832 --> 11:45.008
It's gonna be fine. It's fine.

11:49.796 --> 11:51.536
Here.
Can I just?

11:58.413 --> 11:59.936
There.

11:59.980 --> 12:04.941
Hey, so you can just...

12:04.985 --> 12:07.074
say what I told you.

12:07.117 --> 12:08.815
Go ahead.

12:08.858 --> 12:11.992
Want me t--to your wife?

12:12.035 --> 12:14.995
Whoa, no.
Come on.

12:15.038 --> 12:20.217
"Do you want me to do to you

12:20.261 --> 12:25.179
what we did to Russ' wife?"

12:25.222 --> 12:28.356
Want me to--want me--

12:28.399 --> 12:29.923
You're not listening!

12:29.966 --> 12:31.011
I'm paying you a lot of money

12:31.054 --> 12:32.316
to say one freaking thing

12:32.360 --> 12:34.362
and you're not even
paying attention.

12:34.405 --> 12:40.063
I don't think I can do it!

12:40.107 --> 12:42.587
My mom can.

12:42.631 --> 12:47.418
<i>narrator: Sometimes, the signs</i> <i>
in life are so clear.</i>

12:47.462 --> 12:50.334
<i>If only we knew</i> <i>
how to read them.</i>

12:50.378 --> 12:53.555
You're gonna do it fine.

12:53.598 --> 12:55.122
Okay?

12:55.165 --> 12:58.429
So just--
just listen to my words

12:58.473 --> 13:03.521
and do it again, okay?

13:03.565 --> 13:09.963
<i>both: Want me to do to you</i> <i>
what we did to Russ' wife?</i>

13:10.006 --> 13:11.965
<i>Yes.</i>

13:14.794 --> 13:21.235
<i>♪</i>

13:23.106 --> 13:25.805
Jeez.

13:28.633 --> 13:31.114
Okay, now, you gotta stay
right there.

13:31.158 --> 13:34.422
No, no, back up.
You have to stay right there

13:34.465 --> 13:36.990
for all the microphones
and all that.

13:37.033 --> 13:39.079
<i>♪</i>

13:39.122 --> 13:40.776
You ready?

13:40.820 --> 13:42.038
You just get one shot.

13:42.082 --> 13:44.432
<i>♪</i>

13:44.475 --> 13:46.782
911, what's your emergency?

13:46.826 --> 13:48.436
Hey, hello.

13:48.479 --> 13:50.568
<i>There's someone's</i> <i>
breaking in my house. Help.</i>

13:50.612 --> 13:53.310
<i>And what's the address</i> <i>
you're at?</i>

13:53.354 --> 13:59.534
You want me to do to you
what we did to your wife?

13:59.577 --> 14:01.362
No, I'm not getting
in the car with you.

14:01.405 --> 14:02.363
No, get away.

14:02.406 --> 14:03.843
What's your address?

14:03.886 --> 14:05.322
Get out, get out, get out!

14:05.366 --> 14:07.281
Ma'am.

14:07.324 --> 14:08.848
<i>Ma'am, what's the address</i> <i>
you're at?</i>

14:08.891 --> 14:11.546
Help! Help!

14:11.589 --> 14:14.157
No, no.

14:14.201 --> 14:17.639
<i>Hello? Hello?</i> <i>
Hello, ma'am?</i>

14:17.682 --> 14:21.208
Help! Help! No!

14:37.093 --> 14:39.313
Hello?

14:39.356 --> 14:40.836
He--hello, ma'am?

14:40.880 --> 14:42.751
<i>Ma'am, are you there?</i>
- Yes, I am.

14:42.794 --> 14:46.798
I just shot an intruder
in my house.

14:46.842 --> 14:47.799
Help!

14:50.672 --> 14:52.500
Help! Help!

14:54.894 --> 14:57.984
<i>Hurry, hurry, hurry.</i> <i>
He tried to take me in my car.</i>

14:58.027 --> 14:59.942
<i>He tried to take you</i> <i>
into his car?</i>

14:59.986 --> 15:01.944
<i>He tried to take me</i> <i>
in my car.</i>

15:01.988 --> 15:03.903
<i>Hurry, hurry.</i> <i>
Please don't let him.</i>

15:03.946 --> 15:05.339
Hey, sorry,
can you back it up?

15:05.382 --> 15:06.862
This is sounding off.

15:06.906 --> 15:08.516
- Want it from the beginning?
- Yeah, yeah.

15:08.559 --> 15:09.952
That silence at the top,
is that--

15:09.996 --> 15:11.519
is that playback
or is that the actual call?

15:11.562 --> 15:12.868
No, that's the call.

15:12.912 --> 15:14.652
Not a sound
until I came on the line.

15:14.696 --> 15:16.959
- What's the caller's name?
- Huff.

15:17.003 --> 15:20.006
<i>H-U-F-F.</i>
- All right, run it again.

15:20.049 --> 15:23.096
<i>- 911, what's your emergency?</i> <i>
- Hey, hello.</i>

15:23.139 --> 15:25.011
<i>There's someone's</i> <i>
breaking in my house.</i>

15:25.054 --> 15:26.012
<i>Help.</i>

15:26.055 --> 15:27.143
Hey, just do me a favor.

15:27.187 --> 15:28.623
Send a second car, would you?

15:28.666 --> 15:30.146
Right, thanks.

15:30.190 --> 15:32.322
<i>narrator:</i> <i>
Something about that 911 call</i>

15:32.366 --> 15:35.195
<i>felt off to Detective Hilke.</i>

15:35.238 --> 15:39.242
<i>But who would stage</i> <i>
their own kidnapping?</i>

15:39.286 --> 15:44.204
<i>Certainly, not here,</i> <i>
in a place like this?</i>

15:44.247 --> 15:45.901
<i>What truth would he uncover</i>

15:45.945 --> 15:49.122
<i>inside this well-kept home?</i>

15:49.165 --> 15:51.385
<i>♪</i>

15:51.428 --> 15:54.127
<i>And what lies?</i>

15:55.650 --> 15:59.523
O'Fallon PD.
We're coming in.

15:59.567 --> 16:06.530
<i>♪</i>

16:06.574 --> 16:08.750
Police. Anybody here?

16:08.793 --> 16:10.578
Hello.

16:10.621 --> 16:17.846
<i>♪</i>

16:19.630 --> 16:21.763
Oh, yeah.
Too late for all that.

16:21.806 --> 16:25.636
Already took care of it.

16:27.943 --> 16:29.423
Okay, walk me through
your day today.

16:29.466 --> 16:30.772
Everything that happened.

16:30.815 --> 16:32.774
Well, I always start
with my soda.

16:32.817 --> 16:35.124
Two pumps cherry,
this little punch card.

16:35.168 --> 16:37.431
<i>Ran a bunch of errands,</i> <i>
blah, blah, blah,</i>

16:37.474 --> 16:38.736
<i>all over town.</i>

16:38.780 --> 16:42.436
I get home and I see this truck

16:42.479 --> 16:45.047
sort of waiting for me.

16:45.091 --> 16:47.571
<i>Couldn't quite see the driver.</i>

16:47.615 --> 16:50.357
<i>Kinda heavy, buzz cut.</i>

16:50.400 --> 16:51.967
<i>But soon as I park,</i>

16:52.011 --> 16:54.709
<i>this other guy jumps out</i> <i>
the passenger side</i>

16:54.752 --> 16:56.319
<i>and he runs to my car,</i>

16:56.363 --> 17:00.106
<i>waving this knife around</i> <i>
and stuff. Gets in.</i>

17:00.149 --> 17:02.760
<i>He says, "You're gonna</i> <i>
take me to the bank</i>

17:02.804 --> 17:06.112
<i>"and we're gonna get</i> <i>
Russ' money right now.</i>

17:06.155 --> 17:08.853
<i>So get going</i> <i>
and stuff like that."</i>

17:08.897 --> 17:11.334
<i>"Russ' money."</i> <i>
Do you know a Russ?</i>

17:11.378 --> 17:13.467
<i>No, I don't know any Russ.</i>

17:13.510 --> 17:17.297
<i>So I just knock the knife</i> <i>
out of this guy's hand,</i>

17:17.340 --> 17:18.646
<i>run inside the house.</i>

17:18.689 --> 17:21.475
<i>He's chasing me and stuff.</i>

17:23.694 --> 17:26.915
<i>And I know</i> <i>
I got a gun in the bedroom</i>

17:26.958 --> 17:29.091
<i>so I go straight for it.</i>

17:29.135 --> 17:30.484
<i>And I get the gun.</i>

17:30.527 --> 17:34.009
<i>I call 911.</i> <i>
- 911, what's your emergency?</i>

17:34.053 --> 17:38.709
<i>And then this guy, like,</i> <i>
bursts into my house</i>

17:38.753 --> 17:41.451
<i>and he came at me</i> <i>
and I was like,</i>

17:41.495 --> 17:45.020
<i>"Whoa, hey, get outta here."</i>

17:45.064 --> 17:50.765
<i>And then I shot him.</i>

17:55.465 --> 17:58.773
Okay. I'm very sorry you had
to go through that today.

17:58.816 --> 18:00.427
And thank you
for explaining it to me.

18:00.470 --> 18:01.863
No problem.

18:01.906 --> 18:03.256
I'll have to ask you
a few more questions

18:03.299 --> 18:06.041
down at the station
if that's all right.

18:06.085 --> 18:08.087
Yeah, sure.

18:08.130 --> 18:10.785
Don't wanna go
back in there anyway.

18:10.828 --> 18:13.962
Dead body and all.

18:15.833 --> 18:20.055
But I did see
some sort of paper,

18:20.099 --> 18:23.537
<i>like, sticking out</i> <i>
of his pocket in a baggie.</i>

18:23.580 --> 18:26.888
Maybe you guys could see
what that was.

18:26.931 --> 18:29.369
Will do.
This officer's gonna bring you

18:29.412 --> 18:31.197
down to the station.
I'll be down in a few.

18:31.240 --> 18:33.199
You let her know if you need
anything, all right?

18:33.242 --> 18:34.852
Okay.

18:42.686 --> 18:49.954
<i>♪</i>

19:00.008 --> 19:01.531
Hey, Kerrigan.
- Yeah.

19:01.575 --> 19:04.404
Get a picture of these
and that knife in the car.

19:04.447 --> 19:05.448
Kane, come on in.

19:05.492 --> 19:11.585
<i>♪</i>

19:11.628 --> 19:14.588
<i>What the hell?</i>

19:14.631 --> 19:21.899
<i>♪</i>

19:35.261 --> 19:37.001
Sorry, sir.
This is an active crime scene.

19:37.045 --> 19:40.048
I live here.
My wife called.

19:40.091 --> 19:43.051
Is she all right?
- Your wife is fine.

19:43.094 --> 19:45.140
Okay, there was an intruder

19:45.184 --> 19:46.533
and she was forced
to defend herself

19:46.576 --> 19:50.145
but she's okay.
- What?

19:50.189 --> 19:51.407
What happened?

19:51.451 --> 19:55.585
We're still trying
to figure that out, sir.

19:55.629 --> 19:56.847
That's my son.

19:56.891 --> 19:58.762
He's--well, our son.

19:58.806 --> 20:01.330
Does he--
he live here as well?

20:01.374 --> 20:04.028
No, no, just me and Pam.

20:04.072 --> 20:05.160
Okay.

20:05.204 --> 20:06.379
Well, we'll need
to get your fingerprints

20:06.422 --> 20:08.772
just to clear you.

20:08.816 --> 20:10.687
If that's all right.

20:10.731 --> 20:11.993
No.

20:12.036 --> 20:13.299
No, I don't wanna do that.

20:13.342 --> 20:15.518
It's really just
a formality thing.

20:15.562 --> 20:18.173
No. There's--there's a...

20:18.217 --> 20:20.001
bunch of people
who are after us.

20:20.044 --> 20:22.308
You know, lying and stuff.

20:22.351 --> 20:24.788
There was a murder
a few years back,

20:24.832 --> 20:29.315
and I don't want them trying
to pin that on me or anything.

20:29.358 --> 20:31.665
Hey, well,
this really would just be

20:31.708 --> 20:33.754
to isolate
the intruder's prints.

20:33.797 --> 20:36.060
No.

20:37.584 --> 20:39.847
Excuse me.

20:46.070 --> 20:47.594
Sir, we really need
to keep you back.

20:47.637 --> 20:52.207
Mark?
Mark, what's happening?

20:52.251 --> 20:54.862
Mark? Mark?

20:54.905 --> 20:56.472
Is everything okay?

20:56.516 --> 20:58.822
Yeah, yeah, I guess so.

20:58.866 --> 20:59.954
Well, Pam shot someone?

20:59.997 --> 21:01.869
That's what I heard.

21:01.912 --> 21:04.654
Ma'am,
as I explained earlier,

21:04.698 --> 21:06.221
this is an active crime scene.

21:06.265 --> 21:08.441
You really have to stay back
on your property.

21:08.484 --> 21:09.790
Look, just so you know,

21:09.833 --> 21:11.357
I got lots of stories
about Pam Hupp

21:11.400 --> 21:14.447
and I'm not just talking
about the Betsy Faria business.

21:14.490 --> 21:17.363
I mean, she's always saying
weird stuff.

21:17.406 --> 21:20.409
And I am near positive

21:20.453 --> 21:22.324
that she killed Bushy Tail.

21:22.368 --> 21:24.326
So if you need a witness,
I can be it.

21:24.370 --> 21:26.110
Okay, what did you say
that name was?

21:26.154 --> 21:28.896
- Bushy Tail, my squirrel.
- No, no.

21:28.939 --> 21:32.073
"Pam Hupp?"
H-U-P-P?

21:32.116 --> 21:34.249
Mm-hmm. That's right.

21:34.293 --> 21:35.903
From the Faria case
a while back?

21:35.946 --> 21:37.383
That's right.

21:40.429 --> 21:42.083
<i>♪</i>

21:42.126 --> 21:43.389
Thank you, ma'am.

21:43.432 --> 21:45.260
Please just step back
on your property.

21:45.304 --> 21:46.653
Kerrigan.

21:46.696 --> 21:48.611
Her name's not "Pamela Huff."

21:48.655 --> 21:52.702
It's Pam Hupp.
H-U-P-P.

21:52.746 --> 21:56.184
From that Faria case
a while back?

21:56.227 --> 21:58.839
Yeah, I thought
she looked familiar.

21:58.882 --> 22:00.841
Okay, we really need
to tighten this scene up.

22:00.884 --> 22:02.190
All right? No mistakes.

22:02.233 --> 22:06.586
The press is gonna
be all over this one.

22:06.629 --> 22:09.415
And we're definitely
gonna be on "Dateline."

22:21.209 --> 22:22.602
- Hello? <i>
- Hi, am I speaking with</i>

22:22.645 --> 22:24.517
<i>Russell Faria?</i>
- Yeah.

22:24.560 --> 22:26.606
This is Detective
Sergeant Brian Hilke

22:26.649 --> 22:28.390
over at O'Fallon
Police Department.

22:28.434 --> 22:30.349
<i>Could I get you to come by</i> <i>
at your earliest convenience?</i>

22:30.392 --> 22:32.829
<i>Need to ask you</i> <i>
a few questions.</i>

22:35.658 --> 22:39.575
<i>I'm, uh--</i> <i>
I'm in Florida.</i>

22:39.619 --> 22:41.272
<i>I have to come back</i> <i>
to Missouri?</i>

22:41.316 --> 22:43.274
Yeah.
Yeah, yes.

22:43.318 --> 22:46.408
<i>♪</i>

22:46.452 --> 22:48.758
<i>Reporting live from the home</i> <i>
of Pamela Hupp.</i>

22:48.802 --> 22:51.457
In what police are calling
an ongoing investigation,

22:51.500 --> 22:53.459
we're told that a man
tried to break into this

22:53.502 --> 22:54.982
St. Charles County home

22:55.025 --> 22:56.418
and was shot as a result.

22:56.462 --> 22:58.507
Basically, the whole world
is out there

22:58.551 --> 23:00.683
trying to make a buck.

23:00.727 --> 23:04.426
Did you see all the stuff
the police stole?

23:04.470 --> 23:06.341
A bunch of kitchen crap.

23:06.385 --> 23:08.735
I've never felt so violated.

23:08.778 --> 23:09.953
They took my gun,

23:09.997 --> 23:12.303
like, two stacks of books,
even the cash.

23:12.347 --> 23:14.828
The cash from out
of my nightstand.

23:14.871 --> 23:17.483
They think they can
take my money!

23:17.526 --> 23:21.574
<i>♪</i>

23:21.617 --> 23:22.923
The safe!

23:22.966 --> 23:29.756
<i>♪</i>

23:29.799 --> 23:31.105
Okay.

23:31.148 --> 23:33.455
<i>♪</i>

23:33.499 --> 23:36.458
What'd you tell 'em?

23:36.502 --> 23:37.720
What did I tell who what?

23:37.764 --> 23:40.462
What'd you tell
the police happened?

23:40.506 --> 23:43.073
That Russ hired some guy
to get his money back

23:43.117 --> 23:45.554
and he tried to kill me.

23:49.036 --> 23:51.560
- And they believed you?
- Well, yeah.

23:51.604 --> 23:53.432
'Cause that's what happened.

23:53.475 --> 23:56.304
- - It's just--
- I'm just saying

23:56.347 --> 23:58.611
it took 'em a full week
to arrest Russ

23:58.654 --> 24:00.743
after they brought him in.
You remember that?

24:00.787 --> 24:01.527
And?

24:01.570 --> 24:03.833
And I just wanna know,

24:03.877 --> 24:05.618
is there any chance
that you're in trouble?

24:05.661 --> 24:07.620
I'm the victim here.

24:07.663 --> 24:09.491
You really ought to support me.

24:09.535 --> 24:11.058
Russ is the bad guy.

24:11.101 --> 24:14.148
The police told me
they found a note from Russ

24:14.191 --> 24:15.628
in the guy's pocket.

24:15.671 --> 24:20.328
Lists of stuff to do,
bank accounts, all of it.

24:20.371 --> 24:22.330
Russ should be in jail.

24:25.246 --> 24:32.471
<i>♪</i>

24:34.211 --> 24:36.518
<i>narrator:</i> <i>
Like reliving a nightmare,</i>

24:36.562 --> 24:39.434
<i>Russ was back</i> <i>
in police questioning,</i>

24:39.478 --> 24:41.480
<i>but this time,</i>

24:41.523 --> 24:43.960
<i>with Joel by his side</i> <i>
from the start.</i>

24:44.004 --> 24:46.528
You can go ahead
and close up.

24:47.834 --> 24:50.401
So that's DNA, fingerprints,
handwriting samples.

24:50.445 --> 24:51.664
Anything else you need?

24:51.707 --> 24:54.014
Uh, no, that's it for now.

24:54.057 --> 24:55.929
And I'll have to get copies
of whatever this is.

24:55.972 --> 24:58.845
Oh, uh,
flight records, receipts,

24:58.888 --> 25:01.282
proof that my client
was out of town

25:01.325 --> 25:04.590
before and during
Louis Gumpenberger's murder.

25:04.633 --> 25:07.680
Okay.
We'll check this out.

25:07.723 --> 25:09.508
It'd probably be best
if you stuck around

25:09.551 --> 25:11.510
while we do that.

25:11.553 --> 25:14.469
So I--am I being held?

25:14.513 --> 25:16.558
Like--like, do I have to stay?

25:16.602 --> 25:17.907
No, you're free to go,

25:17.951 --> 25:21.563
but I think it'd be best
if you didn't.

25:21.607 --> 25:23.173
We'll stay.

25:26.220 --> 25:33.444
<i>♪</i>

25:54.640 --> 25:57.338
It's taking too long.

25:57.381 --> 25:58.774
Look, they're just--
they're just going through

25:58.818 --> 26:01.734
all the evidence, okay?

26:01.777 --> 26:03.649
Tracking your cell,
making sure your handwriting

26:03.692 --> 26:07.696
doesn't match
that insane letter.

26:07.740 --> 26:10.612
Just gonna be as open
and helpful as possible, okay?

26:10.656 --> 26:12.919
Yeah.

26:12.962 --> 26:16.052
Last time I was helpful
I spent three years in jail.

26:25.279 --> 26:28.456
Well, Russ,
we appreciate your cooperation.

26:28.499 --> 26:30.893
We're good from our end.

26:30.937 --> 26:33.113
So...

26:33.156 --> 26:34.767
I'm okay?

26:34.810 --> 26:38.205
Russ, you're totally clear.

26:43.210 --> 26:46.126
<i>♪</i>

26:46.169 --> 26:48.650
What were you out doing
last night?

26:50.434 --> 26:52.828
Protecting my financials.

26:53.655 --> 26:55.483
I shouldn't even ask.

26:55.526 --> 26:58.268
Well, a man died
on our carpet, Mark.

26:58.312 --> 26:59.966
Because you shot him.

27:00.009 --> 27:04.231
Defending our home,
like I always do.

27:04.274 --> 27:07.321
Protecting our assets.

27:07.364 --> 27:08.539
What am I supposed to do now?

27:08.583 --> 27:10.237
Police all up in my business.

27:10.280 --> 27:11.978
Well, you know
how it got last time,

27:12.021 --> 27:17.810
telling me what to do
with my accounts and stuff.

27:17.853 --> 27:21.683
I'm just putting
some things away in safekeeping

27:21.727 --> 27:26.253
until all of this
is squared away.

27:26.296 --> 27:28.734
Hmm?

27:48.144 --> 27:52.671
<i>♪</i>

27:52.714 --> 27:54.934
Pamela Hupp,
you're under arrest

27:54.977 --> 27:56.457
for the murder
of Louis Gumpenberger.

27:56.500 --> 27:58.415
Behind your back, please.

27:58.459 --> 28:00.026
<i>♪</i>

28:00.069 --> 28:01.375
All right.

28:01.418 --> 28:04.117
I'll see you for dinner.

28:04.160 --> 28:06.380
Are all those cameras
still out there?

28:06.423 --> 28:07.860
Yes, ma'am.

28:07.903 --> 28:09.557
- Here she comes.
- She's coming out.

28:09.600 --> 28:11.167
There she is, there she is.

28:15.171 --> 28:17.043
How do you feel
about the charges?

28:17.086 --> 28:18.348
Any comment? Any?

28:18.392 --> 28:20.089
Pam, why did you kill
Louis Gumpenberger?

28:20.133 --> 28:21.395
Did you know
Louis Gumpenberger

28:21.438 --> 28:22.657
was a father of two?

28:24.572 --> 28:26.748
Pam, what do you have to say
to the Gumpenberger family?

28:26.792 --> 28:28.707
How many people
have you killed?

28:35.061 --> 28:37.585
Do you have any comment
at all?

28:45.549 --> 28:47.595
<i>narrator: Say hi to Cathy.</i>

28:47.638 --> 28:54.863
<i>♪</i>

28:55.385 --> 28:56.952
It's a little cold.

28:56.996 --> 29:00.042
Could you turn down the AC?

29:02.349 --> 29:05.526
You do understand
you're under arrest for murder.

29:08.572 --> 29:15.362
<i>♪</i>

29:24.458 --> 29:26.503
And you have the right
to an attorney.

29:26.547 --> 29:27.635
If you cannot afford
an attorney,

29:27.678 --> 29:30.203
one will be appointed to you.

29:30.246 --> 29:32.379
And somebody's calling
my lawyer right now?

29:32.422 --> 29:34.555
Yes, that is
happening right now.

29:34.598 --> 29:37.688
And please sign right there
saying I read you your rights.

29:37.732 --> 29:40.256
This font's too small.
Can I have my readers?

29:40.300 --> 29:42.519
They're in my purse.

29:42.563 --> 29:44.304
Oh.

29:44.347 --> 29:47.307
You can borrow mine.

29:47.350 --> 29:49.831
I get 'em at Dollar Tree.

29:49.875 --> 29:51.964
Can't beat those prices.

29:52.007 --> 29:53.835
Is that where you get yours?
- Don't know.

29:53.879 --> 29:56.882
I haven't bought
a new pair in forever.

29:56.925 --> 29:58.318
Okay.

29:58.361 --> 30:00.973
Well, we know
you were at Dollar Tree

30:01.016 --> 30:02.757
because we have your receipt.

30:05.978 --> 30:08.067
You bought a knife?

30:08.110 --> 30:11.505
Well,
I bought a lot of stuff.

30:11.548 --> 30:13.289
Did you know that the knife

30:13.333 --> 30:15.683
that you claim
Louis brandished at you,

30:15.726 --> 30:18.207
that knife is only sold
at Dollar Tree?

30:19.208 --> 30:21.558
I did not know that.

30:21.602 --> 30:24.431
There's Dollar Trees
all over the place.

30:24.474 --> 30:26.215
Practically grow on trees.

30:30.567 --> 30:33.353
Did you know Louis
was not physically capable

30:33.396 --> 30:35.485
of holding that knife

30:35.529 --> 30:38.880
or walking quickly
or running after you?

30:41.013 --> 30:42.536
Well, it's what happened,

30:42.579 --> 30:47.846
so whoever said that
is just plain wrong.

30:47.889 --> 30:52.241
We also have your cell
pinging around Louis' home.

30:52.285 --> 30:54.896
Well, if it was...

30:54.940 --> 30:57.768
by where my shopping was.

30:57.812 --> 30:59.640
And you know
that tracking thing can be off

30:59.683 --> 31:01.337
a lot of the time, you know?

31:01.381 --> 31:03.818
It's a whole big range.

31:03.862 --> 31:08.214
Has to do with towers,
that stuff.

31:08.257 --> 31:09.824
Yeah.

31:09.868 --> 31:12.174
Well, actually,

31:12.218 --> 31:13.741
with Google Waypoint,

31:13.784 --> 31:17.092
we can pinpoint a cell phone
within a few yards.

31:17.136 --> 31:18.789
And we have yours

31:18.833 --> 31:22.619
next to Louis Gumpenberger's
home for four full minutes.

31:24.012 --> 31:25.361
Mm.

31:25.405 --> 31:27.407
Mm, no.

31:27.450 --> 31:30.192
No, that doesn't seem right.

31:30.236 --> 31:32.586
Okay. Well...

31:32.629 --> 31:34.675
let's talk about the $900

31:34.718 --> 31:38.331
that was found
in Louis' pocket.

31:38.374 --> 31:40.855
The serial numbers
of those bills,

31:40.899 --> 31:43.249
they sequentially matched
a hundred-dollar bill

31:43.292 --> 31:46.861
that we found
in your bedside drawer.

31:46.905 --> 31:49.951
<i>And every single killer</i> <i>
in every single book</i>

31:49.995 --> 31:52.127
<i>is caught for the same</i> <i>
stupid reason,</i>

31:52.171 --> 31:54.956
<i>keeping stuff from</i> <i>
the people they kill.</i>

31:55.000 --> 31:59.134
<i>Can you believe that?</i> <i>
It's like, "Hello, idiot."</i>

31:59.439 --> 32:03.660
That's statistically impossible.

32:06.794 --> 32:09.753
Not gonna say nothing else
till my lawyer gets here.

32:09.797 --> 32:11.973
I'm sorry.

32:12.017 --> 32:13.627
That's fine.

32:13.670 --> 32:16.673
I will be right back.
Did you need anything?

32:23.506 --> 32:30.731
<i>♪</i>

32:50.055 --> 32:57.018
<i>♪</i>

34:07.306 --> 34:09.351
Can I go pee?

34:09.395 --> 34:11.223
Let me get a female officer.

34:12.398 --> 34:14.487
You're not gonna pee your pants
or nothing, are you?

34:14.530 --> 34:16.793
No.

35:46.318 --> 35:47.841
Faucet's been on a while.

35:47.884 --> 35:49.321
Yeah, that's what I said.

35:51.497 --> 35:52.628
Hey, let me call you back.

35:52.672 --> 35:59.200
<i>♪</i>

36:01.333 --> 36:03.857
Mrs. Hupp?

36:03.900 --> 36:06.294
Mrs. Hupp, you okay in there?

36:06.338 --> 36:08.253
Mrs. Hupp, if you don't
respond immediately,

36:08.296 --> 36:10.080
we're coming in.

36:10.124 --> 36:12.126
I'm good.

36:20.743 --> 36:23.224
Get help. Hey, Pam?

36:23.268 --> 36:24.486
- Hey!
- Pam?

36:24.530 --> 36:25.574
Hey, get--
get some paper towels.

36:25.618 --> 36:26.749
- Pam!
- Paper towels.

36:26.793 --> 36:27.924
Come on, come on.
- I'm sorry.

36:27.968 --> 36:29.230
- I--
- I didn't know she took the pen.

36:29.274 --> 36:30.666
Pam. Pam, look at me.

36:30.710 --> 36:33.060
Get some pressure.
- Hey, we need help!

36:33.103 --> 36:35.932
- Pam, look at me.
- We need a medic!

36:35.976 --> 36:38.979
Just make sure that poor man

36:39.022 --> 36:40.894
doesn't get in trouble.

36:40.937 --> 36:43.026
Pam, keep looking at me.

36:43.070 --> 36:45.072
Pam, just keep looking at me.

36:45.115 --> 36:46.378
You got medics?

36:46.421 --> 36:48.380
Pam? Pam?

36:48.423 --> 36:54.908
<i>♪</i>

36:54.951 --> 36:57.171
You talk to Mom today?

36:57.215 --> 37:00.174
I think
she's catching a cold.

37:00.218 --> 37:02.263
Poor Mom.

37:02.307 --> 37:05.048
- Good luck with your election.
- Thank you.

37:05.092 --> 37:07.790
How have things been
with Leah lately?

37:08.617 --> 37:10.097
She didn't hit
any vital arteries

37:10.140 --> 37:13.274
or lock the bathroom door.
- Yeah, exactly.

37:13.318 --> 37:15.929
Pam's too narcissistic
to kill herself.

37:15.972 --> 37:18.018
She needed to get out of
the situation that she was in.

37:18.061 --> 37:19.976
She needed to
buy herself some time

37:20.020 --> 37:22.414
to plan her next move
is what she needed to do.

37:22.457 --> 37:24.590
You surprised
she pleaded not guilty?

37:24.633 --> 37:25.591
No.

37:25.634 --> 37:27.070
No, she'll draw it out.

37:29.508 --> 37:32.206
Um, is this seat taken?

37:32.250 --> 37:34.252
Thank you.

37:36.819 --> 37:39.735
Hi. I'm Carol.

37:39.779 --> 37:41.433
Russ.

37:41.476 --> 37:43.435
I know.

37:46.481 --> 37:53.706
<i>♪</i>

